Reasoning: The paper proposes a novel variational autoencoder (VAE) for learning low dimensional embeddings of function classes and performing Bayesian inference for stochastic processes. This involves techniques from machine learning (VAE), artificial intelligence (Bayesian inference), computer vision (spatial interpolation), control systems (stochastic processes), and statistics (statistical inference). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of probabilistic programming languages such as Stan, which falls under the sub-category cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper deals with statistical inference and stochastic processes, which are relevant to the sub-category cs.ST (Statistics).
